{
  "page": "Herrock Kenning",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw\" title=\"House Kenning of Harlaw\"><img alt=\"House Kenning of Harlaw.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg/50px-House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg/75px-House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg/100px-House_Kenning_of_Harlaw.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Herrock Kenning<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Whoreson</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\"><img alt=\"House Kenning of Kayce.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg/50px-House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg/75px-House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg/100px-House_Kenning_of_Kayce.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nHerrock the Whoreson<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_Kayce\" title=\"Knight of Kayce\">Knight of Kayce</a> (possibly)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw\" title=\"House Kenning of Harlaw\">House Kenning of Harlaw</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\">House Kenning of Kayce</a> (founder)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Cultures</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">westermen</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\nIssue<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Herrock Kenning</b>, known as <b>Herrock the Whoreson</b>, was an <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> warrior of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw\" title=\"House Kenning of Harlaw\">House Kenning</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Harlaw\" title=\"Harlaw\">Harlaw</a> who founded <a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\">House Kenning of Kayce</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> His warhorn, the <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Herrock\" title=\"Horn of Herrock\">Horn of Herrock</a>, has been passed down by his descendants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Herrock_Kenning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the wars between the <a href=\"/index.php/Driftwood_king\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Driftwood king\">driftwood kings</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Rock\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Rock\">Kings of the Rock</a>, Herrock the Whoreson used <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Herrock\" title=\"Horn of Herrock\">his horn</a> as a signal for the whores of <a href=\"/index.php/Kayce\" title=\"Kayce\">Kayce</a> to open a postern gate. His men then captured the town for <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. Three different ironborn kings attempted to retake the town over the years; Herrock personally killed two of them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Herrock_Kenning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Iron Islands: Driftwood Crowns.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Kayce.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404174612\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.079 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.272 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 712/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10582/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 8058/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1166/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2169/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usa